By Sept. 1521 (Ep. 1233. 53—43 cf. l. 13311) 5110 was married to william Roper (1496-1578), a member of a Kentish family living at Well Hau, near Eltham (cf. Ep. 104 introd.) ; but was still dwelling, with her husband, in her father’s house. At Christmas 1523 Erasmus dedicated to her some hymns of Prudentius, with a preface which carries congratulations on the birth of their first child. He wrote to her again in 1529 (Lond. xxvi. 50, LB. 1075) ; and her autograph reply is still extant (Breslau MS. Rehd. 254. 129: LB. App. 352).
